    <a href="/reading/proof-writing/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">← back to proofs</a>

    <h1>Direct Proof</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Jim Hefferon · GFDL + CC BY-SA 2.5 · <a href="https://hefferon.net/">Introduction to Proofs</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>direct proof</strong> of "if P then Q" starts by assuming P is true, then deduces Q through a chain of logical steps. Each step follows from definitions, axioms, or previously proven results. No detours, no contradictions: just a straight line from hypothesis to conclusion.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Linear chain P → step1 → step2 → Q -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 420 80" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- P -->
        <rect x="10" y="24" width="60" height="32" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="40" y="45" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="14">P</text>
